#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:5
msgid "Specific Browser Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:7
msgid ""
"This page lists some of the differences between the latest versions of the "
"major browsers that are relevant to Emscripten-compiled applications and "
"games:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:9
msgid ""
"The function :c:func:`emscripten_get_now` returns a wallclock time as a "
"``float`` in milliseconds. *Opera 12.16* and `Windows Google Chrome "
"28.0.1500.95 <https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=158234>`_ "
"have a limitation that the timer precision is only in milliseconds. On other "
"major browsers (*IE10*, *Firefox 22*, *Chrome 28* on non-Windows) it has sub-"
"millisecond precision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:10
msgid "WebGL is not fully supported on *Internet Explorer*:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:12
msgid ""
"*Internet Explorer 10* and older do not support WebGL. Trying to initialize "
"a GL context via EGL, GLUT, SDL or similar will fail. Emscripten "
"applications that do not depend on OpenGL can still run on this browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:13
msgid ""
"*Internet Explorer 11* supports only part of WebGL 1.0. Some commands, "
"shaders etc. may not work. You may be able to limit your app to using the "
"subset that is supported by IE11."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:14
msgid ""
"WebGL support on other major browsers is fairly good (see `WebGL support in "
"different browsers <http://caniuse.com/#feat=webgl>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:16
msgid ""
"*Opera 12.16* has limited support for the W3C File API. In particular it "
"does not support `createObjectURL functionality <http://www.opera.com/docs/"
"specs/presto2.12/apis/#file>`_, which means that it is not possible to use "
"the browser's image codecs to decode preloaded files in the Emscripten "
"virtual file system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/guidelines/browser_limitations.rst:17
msgid ""
"OpenAL and SDL audio support in Emscripten depend on the Web Audio API (see "
"`Web Audio API support in different browsers <http://caniuse.com/#feat=audio-"
"api>`_)."
msgstr ""
